        Clause 76 [<span class="italic">Recovery of certain fugitive children</span>]:
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0564P0-07345'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0564P0_19950613_GCR_118' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        <span class="member">The Earl of Lindsay</span> moved Amendment No. 195:
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0564P0-07346'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0564P0_19950613_GCR_119' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        Page 63, line 12, leave out ("or the Channel Islands").
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0564P0-07347'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0564P0_19950613_GCR_120' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        The noble Earl said: Government Amendment No. 206 clarifies the way in which the provisions of the Bill will extend to the Channel Islands. New subsection (9) of Clause 96 provides that
        <q>Her Majesty may by order in council direct that any of the relevant provisions specified &#x2026; shall extend &#x2026; to any of the Channel Islands".</q>
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0564P0-07348'>
